# GDScript Class Definition Order

- Before finishing any new or edited `.gd` file, verify declarations follow Godot/GDScript ordering expected by gdlint.
- Before marking work complete, run `gdlint` on every edited `.gd` file (or `gdlint` on the project) so `class-definitions-order` and other gdtoolkit-only checks are caught.
- Keep top-level script structure consistent:
  1) `class_name` and `extends`
  2) `signal`
  3) `enum`
  4) `const`
  5) exported vars
  6) plain vars
  7) onready vars
  8) lifecycle methods (`_init`, `_ready`, `_process`, `_physics_process`, etc.)
  9) public methods
  10) private helpers
  11) inner classes
- Avoid mixing constants, vars, and methods in interleaved order.
- For files with inner classes, place them after primary script logic unless project conventions for that file require otherwise.
- If uncertain, reorder declarations to satisfy `gdlint` before considering the change complete.
